\pard\widctlpar\fi660\sl276\slmult1\par

\pard\widctlpar\sl276\slmult1\i\ldblquote Magdalena de Luna\'85\rdblquote\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi660\sl276\slmult1\i0\ldblquote Who\rquote s there?\rdblquote\par
Darkness. Smoke. Vapour. The smell burned her nostrils.\par
\i\ldblquote Magdalena\'85\rdblquote\par
\i0 The voice was deep and whispering, and Magda couldn\rquote t tell where it was coming from.\par
She stood up, and reached for her sword. How had she gotten here?\par
\i\ldblquote Do you wish to fly, Magda?\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote It\rquote s \lquote your Grace\rquote  to you,\rdblquote  she said.\par
The voice laughed, wheezing like a dead animal\rquote s lung deflating. It made Magda\rquote s skin crawl.\par
\i\ldblquote I\rquote d like to thank you for the sacrifice. It whetted my appetite\'85 for a moment.\rdblquote\par
\i0 A clammy hand rested on her shoulder and she jumped, but when she looked, there was nobody there.\par
She swallowed. \ldblquote You.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote Yes\'85\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote So I\rquote m dead,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote Well. It was a good life.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote Not a long one though,\rdblquote\i0  Asmodeus said. \i\ldblquote Such a shame you could not do everything you\rquote d hoped for. You had such fire in you.\rdblquote\par
\i0 She gripped the sword tighter. \ldblquote I have no regrets.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote The plague is ravaging your country still.\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote It\rquote s not my country anymore. It died with me.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote Such a pity no-one has the strength to extinguish the zombie horde.\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote Get to the point, Lord of the Damned.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote You\rquote re not actually dead yet, my dear,\rdblquote  \i0 Asmodeus said. \i\ldblquote Though nearly. Very nearly. In the Material Plane, your body is still burning. Though not beyond the power of one such as me to restore.\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote What do you want?\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote Your life.\rdblquote\par
\i0\ldblquote I already gave you it.\rdblquote\par
\i\ldblquote No, no, no,\rdblquote  he purred. \ldblquote I don\rquote t want you to die for me. I want you to live for me. I want you to look at me, in the face, and tell me you\rquote ll carry me in your heart.\rdblquote\par
\i0 A figure emerged from the fog. Tall, and thin, and clad in red. His eyes burned like coals in a skull that floated over his body.\par
\i\ldblquote I\rquote ll take your soul at the end. But in the meantime, you wipe out those undead in my name. Send them back to me. Bring order.\rdblquote\par
\i0 Around them, visions of zombies, climbing over her homeland. Of it being carved into pieces by nobles who had waited for her country to die.\par
\i\ldblquote Do we have a deal?\rdblquote\i0\par
Magdalena shook the devil\rquote s hand.\par
\par

