\pard\widctlpar\sl276\slmult1\i 20 years later\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi660\sl276\slmult1\i0\par

\pard\widctlpar\sl276\slmult1 Dying. Again. Bleeding out by the side of the road like a vagrant. Just another vampire spawn, one of hundreds over the years.\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi660\sl276\slmult1 It was no way for a lady of good breeding to die, she thought.\par
She clasped the unholy symbol of Asmodeus around her belt, for all the good it would do her. Her Channel Divinity was burned, her magic reserves depleted.\par
She pushed the corpse of the vampire spawn off of her, pulling the stake from its heart before clasping her hand to the wound.\par
She clambered to her feet, just in time to see the sun starting to crest the horizon.\par
She smiled. Unbelievable.\par
Once again, against all odds, she lived to see another day.\par
And just when she was wondering to herself how she\rquote d managed not to bleed out, the first beam of morning sunlight warmed her skin.\par
She began to burn.\par
\par

