\pard\widctlpar\sl276\slmult1\par
She spent a solid two hours skimming through books on how to kill vampires.\par

\pard\widctlpar\fi660\sl276\slmult1 Who was she now? What good was she? She\rquote d given her soul for this life. This purpose. And now she was that she had spent her life\rquote s work hunting.\par
\i Vampires are immortal, driven only by the need for the blood of humans.\par
Vampires tend to come in broods \f1\emdash\f0  one vampire controlling many spawn.\par
Vampires reproduce by transforming humans into other vampires.\par
\i0 A realisation was starting to come over her.\par
She was immortal.\par
She could feel Asmodeus fizzing in anger inside her unholy symbol, and she smiled. He hadn\rquote t counted on this. Oh, he wasn\rquote t getting her soul for a \i long\i0  time.\par
Her soul was damned, multiple times over \f1\emdash\f0  but maybe some good could come of it.\par
\ldblquote Find what you\rquote re looking for?\rdblquote  the old man said, poking his head round the corner.\par
\ldblquote Not yet. But you\rquote re right. I don\rquote t feel so helpless now,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote My answers are in one of these books, and I\rquote m going to read through every single one until I find them.\rdblquote\par
\ldblquote It\rquote ll take a while.\rdblquote  He gestured to the library. It seemed to stretch out beyond the horizon. The bookcases loomed over them, seemed to bend towards them, blocking out the light.\par
Magda smiled. \ldblquote I have nothing left but time now.\rdblquote  \i\f2\par

